{"author":{"id":"cad0afbc936f740fb6048ec11d7d44bbdf0daf9970a4dbb5cf01894d5825487d"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1705042028,"nonce":"ydLL6PIya5IhkGAvg2oKGLh/weI=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOAW4Y0s57mAjBzlHZwr0"},"target":"bed2672b6736519b0c8119dc5432eb5479deaba829cbf5792e47b36d3ee3b253","message":"Issue with Trimmomatic output log files: \n\nSummary: can outputs be renamed differently? \n\nRunning on Galaxy Australia, Trimmomatic version 0.36.6\n\nInputs: Paired-end reads: 2 collections (one of R1 files, one of R2 files)\n\nOutput required: Trimmed reads, and a collection of log files (not trimlog files). \n\n(Edited to update with a more general problem with output file naming, not only relevant to output log files)\n\nIssue: when input files are named in the format `sample123_R1.fastqsanger` and `sample123_R2.fastqsanger`, output file names all take on the former name only, e.g. `sample123_R1.fastqsanger`\n\nI think it would be better if outputs (where they refer to both R1 and R2 files) could be labelled without the R1 extension, such as `sample123.fastqsanger`\n\nThis would be clearer for the user, and also for downstream tools (such as plots in MultiQC, which are thus also labelled as being R1 files, when they are actually relating to both R1 and R2 files).","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1704860907,"nonce":"+tagPwhPxsKT3h/2FZ3EAqgT8n0=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5wTjGZ","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5703#issuecomment-1884172697"},"message":"I don't know if this is related to the issue about element identifiers? https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1595\n\nposting in case it might be.","files":null}]}